Title: Few observations related to depositpaid field validations

1. Gave false as value:
Request Body:
{
   "roomid": 35,
   "firstname": "ABC",
  "lastname": "DEF",
  "depositpaid": false,
  "bookingdates": {
    "checkin": "2025-11-01",
    "checkout": "2025-11-02"
  },
  "email": "abc.def@example.com",
  "phone": "12345678900"
}

Expected Behavior:
Error stating deposit should be paid.

Actual Behavior:
201 Created

Response Body:
{
    "bookingid": 5,
    "roomid": 35,
    "firstname": "ABC",
    "lastname": "DEF",
    "depositpaid": false,
    "bookingdates": {
        "checkin": "2025-11-01",
        "checkout": "2025-11-02"
    }
}

2. Tried with Numeric char type than boolean for depositpaid field,
server accepts it and changes it to true in response.
Request Body:
{
   "roomid": 36,
   "firstname": "ABC",
  "lastname": "DEF",
  "depositpaid": 123,
  "bookingdates": {
    "checkin": "2025-11-01",
    "checkout": "2025-11-02"
  },
  "email": "abc.def@example.com",
  "phone": "12345678900"
}

Response Body:
{
    "bookingid": 6,
    "roomid": 36,
    "firstname": "ABC",
    "lastname": "DEF",
    "depositpaid": true,
    "bookingdates": {
        "checkin": "2025-11-01",
        "checkout": "2025-11-02"
    }
}

3. if we send true and false as String values("true", "false") in depositpaid field,
server accepts it and booking is getting created.